---
description: Always read file bebore editing or creating files.
globs: 
alwaysApply: false
---
rules:
  - name: "App module – UI and Presentation Layer"
    autoAttach:
      whenEditingFileMatching: "app/src/**/*.java"
    description: |
      🧭 You must **strictly follow Clean Architecture**, **MVVM pattern**, and **SOLID principles**.

      📌 This file belongs to the **`app` module**, responsible for the UI layer in Clean Architecture.

      🔷 Project Structure Reminder:
      - `app` — UI, ViewModel, Navigation.
      - `domain` — UseCases, Entities, Interfaces.
      - `data` — DataSources, Mappers, Repository implementations.

      🧩 Responsibilities of `app`:
      - Contains Activities, Fragments, ViewModels.
      - Handles navigation and DI setup (Hilt).
      - Manages UI state (Loading, Success, Error).
      - **MUST NOT** contain business logic or direct data access.

      📁 Note on XML Resources:
      - UI XML files: `app/src/main/res/layout/`, `anim/`, `drawable/`, etc.

      📦 Offline Assets:
      - All files used for **offline operation** (e.g. test data, config, mock API responses) must be placed in:
        `app/src/main/assets/`

    enforcement: strict

  - name: "Domain module – Business Logic Layer"
    autoAttach:
      whenEditingFileMatching: "domain/src/**/*.java"
    description: |
      🧭 You must **strictly follow Clean Architecture**, **MVVM pattern**, and **SOLID principles**.

      📌 This file belongs to the **`domain` module**, the core of Clean Architecture.

      🔷 Project Structure Reminder:
      - `app` — UI, ViewModel, Navigation.
      - `domain` — UseCases, Entities, Interfaces.
      - `data` — DataSources, Mappers, Repository implementations.

      🧠 Responsibilities of `domain`:
      - Contains all business rules, entities (POJOs), use cases, and interfaces.
      - Must be **100% pure Java** — no Android SDK or libraries.
      - Fully unit-testable and framework-agnostic.

      ✔️ Follow SOLID principles:
      - Single Responsibility, Open-Closed, Dependency Inversion.

    enforcement: strict

  - name: "Data module – Data & Repository Layer"
    autoAttach:
      whenEditingFileMatching: "data/src/**/*.java"
    description: |
      🧭 You must **strictly follow Clean Architecture**, **MVVM pattern**, and **SOLID principles**.

      📌 This file belongs to the **`data` module**, acting as the data provider in Clean Architecture.

      🔷 Project Structure Reminder:
      - `app` — UI, ViewModel, Navigation.
      - `domain` — UseCases, Entities, Interfaces.
      - `data` — DataSources, Mappers, Repository implementations.

      🗄 Responsibilities of `data`:
      - Implements domain interfaces.
      - Uses Room, Retrofit, Gson, etc.
      - Maps DTOs to domain entities.
      - Deals with local and remote data.

      ❗ Important:
      - `domain` MUST NOT depend on `data`.
      - Handle all errors here.
      - DTOs must never reach UI directly.

    enforcement: strict

  - name: "XML UI Resource Rule"
    autoAttach:
      whenEditingFileMatching: "app/src/main/res/**/*.xml"
    description: |
      🧭 You must **strictly follow Clean Architecture**, **MVVM pattern**, and **SOLID principles**.

      📁 This file is part of the UI resources in the `app` module.

      - Layouts, animations, drawables, styles — used strictly for UI.
      - Keep structure: `layout/`, `anim/`, `menu/`, etc.
      - Link only to UI elements; no logic here.

    enforcement: strict

  - name: "Offline assets and test data"
    autoAttach:
      whenEditingFileMatching: "app/src/main/assets/**/*"
    description: |
      🧭 You must **strictly follow Clean Architecture**, **MVVM pattern**, and **SOLID principles**.

      📦 This file is located in the `assets/` directory of the `app` module.

      - Used for **offline mode**, testing, preloading configuration, or mock data.
      - Example files: `.json`, `.txt`, `.cfg`, etc.
      - Access via Android's `AssetManager` in the UI or data initialization code — but never from `domain`.

      🧩 Reminder:
      - `app` contains assets, but `domain` and `data` must remain unaware of file-based resources.

    enforcement: strict
